l about one another.<br /><br />Look, it's not a great thing about the world. But countries fundamentally can't trust each other at a very deep level. This isn't to say that all these revelations aren't going to do real damage to the US, or that the US surveillance apparatus isn't in some way out of control (especially if the President didn't know about this, and especially in terms of domestic surveillance). But if you expect countries not to spy on one another or think that this is somehow avoidable by just voting nicer people into office, you haven't thought very hard about the incentives facing leaders.

              

              
              
